Sentencas: Brownmillerite oxide Ca2Fe1.3Mn0.7O5+delta is synthesized and evaluated as a new cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Evaluation of a brownmillerite oxide as cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The average thermal expansion coefficient (TEC) of Ca2Fe1.3Mn0.7O5+delta is 13.3 +/- 0.2 x 10(-6) K-1, close to that of the typical electrolyte materials.
Titulo: Evaluation of a brownmillerite oxide as cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The lowest polarization resistance (Rp) (0.22 +/- 0.02 Omega cm(2) at 750 degrees C in air) and cathodic overpotential values are achieved when the material is sintered at 1000 degrees C on Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 (CGO) electrolyte.
Titulo: Evaluation of a brownmillerite oxide as cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Two main oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) processes are identified.
Titulo: Evaluation of a brownmillerite oxide as cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The rate limiting step for ORR is found to depend on the oxygen partial pressure.
Titulo: Evaluation of a brownmillerite oxide as cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The excellent electrochemical performance indicates that Ca2Fe1.3Mn0.7O5+delta can be a promising cathode material for SOFCs.
Titulo: Evaluation of a brownmillerite oxide as cathode for solid oxide fuel cells
